The author of the article is Ricky Harris, a sophomore studying Computer Science at Pace University. He is also a member of the Summer 2017 White House Internship Program in the Office of Digital Strategy. Ricky describes his experience as a White House intern and compares it to being a NCAA Cross Country athlete, highlighting the high level of energy and dedication required in both roles. He expresses gratitude for the opportunity to communicate messages directly to the American people and states that he will continue to approach life with high energy and a winning attitude.